http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Man-disrupts-KJP-leader%E2%80%99s-press-meet/article14009335.ece

Karnataka Janata Paksha (KJP) leader Prasanna Kumar’s press conference here on Tuesday was disrupted by a BJP supporter, who took serious objection to the personal remarks made against former CM B. S. Yeddyurappa.After Mr. Prasanna Kumar, flanked by his party workers, allegedly began passing personal remarks against Mr. Yeddyurappa, the supporter went up to the stage and shouted at him. However, police personnel brought him out of the venue.“The man was disrupting the press conference … the police personnel brought him out of the venue. He was later let off,” a police officer added.